name: AWCameraPreview
desc: A widget showing a live camera preview of the Aware Flutter Face Capture SDK

name: AWCameraPreview
desc: Creates a preview widget for the given instance of FaceCapture, Workflow, username and timeout values.

name: cameraOrientation
desc: An enumeration of the possible camera orientations including CameraOrientation.portrait and CameraOrientation.landscape

name: cameraPosition
desc: This is an enumeration representing either the front facing camera or the main (back) camera of a device.

name: captureTimeOut
desc: The capture timeout of the given FaceCapture instance. A timeout of 0.0 indicates there is no timeout.

name: createState
desc: Creates the mutable state for this widget at a given location in the tree.

name: feedbackTextstyle
desc:
Face Capture's SDK offers feedback on how a user should better orient themselves to allow for an effective Face Capture.
This is returned as a string that can be fully customized.

name: imagePreviewShape
desc:
Image preview shape dictates the clipping shape of the image presented during the the face capture session.
The options include

name: layoutWidget
desc:
Use the layoutWidget to determine the layout of the image preview in relation to the feedback messages.
The default layout is a stack with the feedback message overlayed on top of the image preview.

name: previewPosition
desc:
If layoutWidget is set then this is value of 1 or 2 determins the position of the image preview in the layout widget relative to that of the feedback text
Example: Setting 1 with a LayoutWidget.column puts the camera preview at the top of the column.

name: selectedCamera
desc: Selected Camera for Face Capture to use to get frames.

name: username
desc: The username of the person whose face is being registered for the given instance of FaceCpature.

name: iconLeading
desc: Icon of leading widget on the appbar.

name: onLeadingButtonPressed
desc:
Function called when leading icon button is pressed.
Please note that a press of the leading icon will always stop the face capture session and navigate back.
OnLeadingButtonPressed is excecuted before the face capture session is stopped.
